cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a novel solution for real-time Non-Linear Model Predictive Control (NMPC) and validates it in a simulation environment using an UAV platform. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed controller can be applied to control the motion of robots and UAVs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an efficient solver for NMPC, which can be used in various AI applications such as autonomous driving and robotics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a Least Square formulation to make the solver time-efficient, which is a common technique in machine learning. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper also releases the implementation of the proposed approach as open source C++ code, which can be useful for software engineering applications.
